<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="369" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/717.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-09">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 9, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Disorders in Habana and suburbs have for some days been assuming
                            character of race war. In spite of threats to deal severely with
                            trouble-makers, the authorities are showing weakness. Americans, other
                            foreigners, and many Cubans extremely apprehensive and appeal for
                            sending of a war vessel. The size of our colony and large number of
                            American women it contains places heavy responsibility upon our
                            Government as regards possible consequences of racial trouble. I feel
                            that a war vessel should be sent immediately for moral effect and to
                            calm general apprehension.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>